title: Police say Liverpool parade collision not terrorism
description: The Merseyside Police have said that the incident of a car colliding with pedestrians in Liverpool city center during Liverpool Football Club's Premier League victory parade is not being treated as terrorism.
author: Beth Lindop

title: SEC's Sankey: Not settled on preferred CFP format
description: SEC commissioner Greg Sankey said Monday at the league's annual meetings that he's open-minded about the format of the College Football Playoff, while leaving some breadcrumbs about what he thinks are priorities in the conference's decision-making.
author: Pete Thamel

title: 'It missed us by inches': Witnesses describe car driving into crowd at Liverpool title parade
description: An off-duty BBC reporter who was attending the parade called it "hell on Earth".

title: 'Poor' decision by PGMOL to pick Bramall for Villa game - Hackett
description: The referees' body made a "poor management decision" in appointing Thomas Bramall to officiate Aston Villa's defeat by Manchester united, says former referees' boss Keith Hackett.

title: 'I've not been feeling great' - Raducanu battles illness to set up Swiatek clash
description: Emma Raducanu overcame a lengthy medical time-out during a gutsy three-set first-round victory at the French Open to set up a blockbuster meeting with four-time champion Iga Swiatek.

title: Villa make official complaint to PGMOL after referee howler costs them CL
description: Aston Villa have made an official complaint to the PGMOL over the selection of referee Thomas Bramall for their Premier League final-day match against Man Utd, which Champions League-chasing Villa lost after having a goal controversially ruled out.

title: Calvin Ridley praises Tennessee Titans' offseason program: 'We're competing'
description: Wide receiver Calvin Ridley discusses the Tennessee Titans' offseason program and offers his thoughts and praise for how things are going.

title: Sean O'Malley's coach talks working with 'black belt in the clinch' Demetrious Johnson
description: Sean O'Malley has sought help from one of the greatest fighters of all time ahead of UFC 316.
